to the editor re times 's 2 top editors resign after furor on writer 's fraud front page june 6 i am 81 years old for most of my life the new york times has been the institution in our country in which i have had the most confidence the current crisis culminating in the resignations of howell raines the executive editor and gerald m boyd the managing editor saddens and hurts me just as a crisis in my personal family would but just as a crisis in my family would not neither does this crisis at the times destroy my confidence in the newspaper and in its future willard dalrymple georgetown me june 6 2003

